text_content:
We need to replace our custom google sheets implementation with the singer tap since we have multiple issues:

Google Picker doesn't work if Ad-blocker is activated and is in general not very reliable
Google Picker only works for the person who logs in in the first place and not for anybody else in the company
We cannot import just single tabs but need to implement the whole sheet

https://github.com/singer-io/tap-google-sheets

integration: get requirements for a good amazon integration

text_content:
Our customer Oatsome is requesting a new table/endpoint. 
It's the Giftcard endpoint. On Shopify you can sell giftcards which can be used to buy products from the Shopify shop. A crucial information this table can deliver is the remaining balance on the giftcard.
This table is used by the customer's finance department to understand what are the open balances on customers giftcards they can still use as a substitue of cash.

https://shopify.dev/api/admin-rest/2021-10/resources/gift-card#resource_object

text_content:
Our customer Everdrop is reporting that the import of the Shopify discount code table takes very long to import. He gets the error message msg="Too Many Requests".

Please also see his feedback in the screenshot. The assumed issue is that each discount code gets queried and in their case they have more than 1000+ codes. Apparently there is a limit of 4q/s => would take very long to finish

text_content:
for twitter it looks like they only allow oauth 1: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/authentication/oauth-1-0a/obtaining-user-access-tokens (the oauth 2 is only for "app level signups")

we probably could use this library: https://github.com/thephpleague/oauth1-client/blob/master/resources/examples/twitter.php

but the sample uses sessions, we would have to get it in the state as part of the url.

in the datasource-api it would have to be handled inside of this controller: https://github.com/goes-funky/datasource-api/blob/develop/app/Http/Controllers/OAuthHandler.php
description:
for twitter it looks like they only allow oauth 1: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/authentication/oauth-1-0a/obtaining-user-access-tokens (the oauth 2 is only for "app level signups")

we probably could use this library: https://github.com/thephpleague/oauth1-client/blob/master/resources/examples/twitter.php

in the datasource-api it would have to be handled inside of this controller: https://github.com/goes-funky/datasource-api/blob/develop/app/Http/Controllers/OAuthHandler.php

text_content:
need to figure out how the node pool scaling works (it shuts down servers within 10min, so the tap would have to stop by then)
only "disruptable" imports may run on that nodes, others not
the "kafka subscriber" could then send it's state (run_id, postions,..) and the last state message into a topic, and the job broker restarts it from another server

integration: Quickbooks: Add support for Minor Version 62, there are missing columns
text_content:
QuickbooksOnline API sometimes adds new columns in different tables. When the MinorVersion is not in the request, the API will not return these columns. 
As an example, I am using the "SKU" column in Items. This column is released in the MinorVersion:4.
We do not return this column:  
 

There are some more columns in different tables which are dependent on MinorVersion.

integration: Check All Integrations/Tables for replication_key field
text_content:
For each of below integrations it is needed to be checked all related taps and respective tables that are using created_at as replication_key.
For all tables that are using created_at as replication_key, we need to verify if the stream supports filtering by updated_at field in order to replace it with that (replace created_at with updated_at). 
Check if there are streams using updated_at as replication key but the merge table has not been activated, if so activate the merge option and test it.
In case when for respective tables do not support filtering by updated_at field we should enforce the table to execute only full_import and should not support incremental import any more.
Please be careful: In case when the tables are using only created_at as replication_key and the data stored in that table are never updated (for instace: log data) it's no need to replace it or to enforce full-incremental

"Profiles" provides all the data attributes for a person, based on the Klaviyo Person ID.
Currently, we can only extract "profiles" information from the events data which is quite massive. 

This data would enable the customer to track his/her subscriber development without processing millions of rows.

I've suggested to the customer to extract this column into a separate table with an ID so he can import this big JSON column as a separate table and join both tables later on. 

But it would be ideal if we could make it happen in the integration to import the whole table as one.

FYI: This integration can be co-built with the lead's tech lead

Hi there, 

I spoke with the lead and we're exactly what they're looking for. The trouble is, they have many, many sources, but luckily they only need one integration.

They serve a number of companies with a range of different services. From all these different services (and companies), they use Outsystems to capture data, and then send this data to SaaS apps such as Salesforce, Airtable and so on. 

What they'd like to do is bring in the data from Outsystems into y42. 

At your earliest convenience, can you please see if what the development would like to bring in data from Outsystems:

https://success.outsystems.com/Documentation/11_x_platform/Reference/OutSystems_APIs

integration: Integrations that that require Oauth, like Google Analytics, FAcebook Ads or Facebook pages remain in status Screening for available table if not refreshed
text_content:
Steps to reproduce the bug:

Environments: Production, Dev

1- Add a Google Analytics, FAcebook Ads or Facebook pages integration.
2- Authenticate
3- Notice that it will remain forever in the status screening for available tables and columns. if not refreshed

integration: Microsoft Azure SQL Database - Discuss true incremental Update
text_content:
Our customer TMNZ works with a Microsoft Azure SQL Database. They are doing a daily full import on this database that takes them 7h to complete. 

Why full import?
Customer: "Our data can change for any given historic records at any time. So we can't really use incremental imports.
Even already CLOSED items can be changed in some cases.
And also - same historical data can be used to calculate balances so we cant skip them or calculate separately (or from db point of view - to store them on differ, less used partition)"

-> Is there a chance that we could create a true incremental Update for this database?

OR is there another option to shorten the Orchestration time? Are there significant performance differences between views, tables, hosting region, etc. ?

integration: Pinterest - a lot of columns are null although they should be filled
text_content:

Our customer Charlotte from Everdrop reported that in the table pin_promotion_delivery_metrics  a lot of columns like

campaign_name
campaign_id
ad_group_name
ad_group_id 
are just empty although they shouldn't. A pin (similar to an ad) is always related to a campaign and an ad_group, therefore, a pin always should have a campaign_name or campaign_id.
But in the table all rows are empty.

Python library https://github.com/mkleehammer/pyodbc/wiki

Code Example (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-sql/database/connect-query-python?tabs=macos)
import pyodbc
server = '<server>.database.windows.net'
database = '<database>'
username = '<username>'
password = '<password>'   
driver= '{ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server}'

with pyodbc.connect('DRIVER='+driver+';SERVER='+server+';PORT=1433;DATABASE='+database+';UID='+username+';PWD='+ password) as conn:
    with conn.cursor() as cursor:
        cursor.execute("SELECT TOP 3 name, collation_name FROM sys.databases")
        row = cursor.fetchone()
        while row:
            print (str(row[0]) + " " + str(row[1]))
            row = cursor.fetchone()

From Michael of Waterdrop:
we were looking into the available tables and searched for a table called Item_group, because we want a detailed information of the components for each set. But we couldn't find a table like that.
In short we want to aggregate all the components a set consists of, so we can sum up the costs. We thought we can use "Items" and "Item_group" to do that, but we can't find the tables. Do you have any ideas how to do that?
Here is the description of the tables:
https://www.netsuite.com/help/helpcenter/en_US/srbrowser/Browser2020_2/odbc/record/itemgroup.html
https://www.netsuite.com/help/helpcenter/en_US/srbrowser/Browser2020_2/odbc/record/item.html


Both tables are included in a single table InventoryItem but can be split into smaller tables based on Item type

text_content:
Important reports

GET_AMAZON_FULFILLED_SHIPMENTS_DATA_GENERAL
GET_V2_SETTLEMENT_REPORT_DATA_FLAT_FILE

Workflow for GET_AMAZON_FULFILLED_SHIPMENTS_DATA_GENERAL:
-Split the date range from start_date to now in monthly date ranges
-Create report for each date range, wait for the import to finish processing, retrieve the data
-Repeat for each date range
-Save the last end date in state

Workflow for GET_V2_SETTLEMENT_REPORT_DATA_FLAT_FILE:
The report type can not be requested, they are created automatically by amazon each day. All the reports saved by amazon go roughly 3 month back.
-Get all imports created by amazon
-Retrieve data for each of them
-Save the last import id in the state

Our customer "Von Fred" is a marketing agency 
the customer is doing online marketing ads for several customers
The customers are granting "Von Fred" access to their Facebook account so they can create Ads
Von Fred's clients can also withdraw permissions again
Currently, Von Fred is having 1 integration for several Facebook accounts
They are experiencing failed imports because among several accounts there might be an account where access is withdrawn (see screenshot)

The full import implemenation of typeform integration creates 3 tables (landing, questions, answers) for each form created in typeform.
When the customers creates very often new forms in Typeform a lot of new tables get added every couple of days and they always need to manually reconnect the integration Schema and manually put new input nodes into the models. text_content:
After talking to a customer, I was researching on the possibility to get the UTM data for an order.  UTM data is providing information about from which marketing channel and marketing campaign an order is actually coming from.
In this 2 community discussions I found out that Shopify is offering the access to "Customer Visits" data:

https://community.shopify.com/c/Shopify-APIs-SDKs/Access-to-UTM-campaign-fields-via-API/td-p/543076
https://community.shopify.com/c/Shopify-APIs-SDKs/How-to-get-the-UTM-parameters-associated-with-the-order-through/td-p/913410

And here in the Shopify GraphQL documentation I found something suitable: https://shopify.dev/api/admin/graphql/reference/discounts-and-marketing/customervisit
The first community article actually describes how you could build this on order level.

integration: Facebook Ads - Conversion data seem to be mismatched/not correct
text_content:
A customer (von Fred) is reporting that he is experiencing inconsistency in the Facebook Ads data. 
In this case it's about the "ads_insights" table. 
The customer has added the table to datos-d. This is the integration. 
I've created a model and extracted the data and have visualised it here.
The customer has provided us with a data export his got from our competitor Supermetrics. The data is here.

So in detail:
So for example when we take 2021-09-02 for ad_name: "0806_BR_Jobmatch"
in y42 we have:
PC_Like: 1
PC_Registration: NULL
PC_funnel: 5
in the data from Supermetrics provided by the customer via Google Sheet we have:
PC_Like Gastro:	1
PC_Registration_Gastro: 2	
PC_Funnel_1_Gastro: 5
=> so we don't have any data for this day and for this ad_name for PC_Registration_Gastro


another example:
2021-09-01 for ad_name: "0806_BR_Schnellkoch"
in y42:
PC_Like: NULL
PC_Registration: NULL
PC_funnel: 4
in Supermetrics:
PC_Like Gastro:	NULL
PC_Registration_Gastro: NULL
PC_Funnel_1_Gastro: 5


Summary: So when the customer pulls conversion data from y42, it seems like he doesn't get most updated data. We have conversion data showing for these ads but it seems like that they are not updated.

text_content:
We have a customer having problems with opportunity_applications table from the Lever integration. 
Inside this table there is a column customquestions. It seems to be a very nested JSON and it seems to be an array of nested objects whereas it includes an object fields which is an array of nested objects.
The object fields which is inside customquestions is also an array of nested objects.
Already on integration level it seems like that fields is not formatted properly as JSON. Thats why further on when modeling with the data and using the JSON extraction node, the node can not format the column correctly as JSON but always just identifies the column as STRING 

The customer is claiming that he does not have any problems with this column using Postman or other API services.

text_content:
We have issues with getting post_insights tables for a customer and also our y42 account. I'm not sure if it is a bug or a problem on the Facebook Side.

I used our y42 Demo Account for testing if we can solve the issue ourselves by adding FB Permissions. I also invited Egi to it, because I hope those Test Connections can help us solve this problem. 

First Test (with a different page Account [neither y42 nor customer]) -  "Rebecca Test - Connection" with a Page Account (not y42), I'm able to get some of the post_insights table (the ones I'm not getting, throw a "monetization permission" error - which should be because of missing permission, so all good)

Second to Eight Test (with the y42 Account, Test 7 is with Monis Account (one owner), Test 8 even with the creator Hai: We are unable to get any post_insights tables. 

----> PERSONAL ASSUMPTION:
the difference between my first test and the other with the y42 account is, that y42 is using the business suite and the first account that I used, not. I think this is causing the FB Pages Integration to work for that account (and also Egi's Test Account) but not the y42 & the customer's account.

So all values are numeric.

integration: MySQL Connector: group tables by database - currently very cluttered
text_content:
The MySQL connector does not nicely group tables by database. 
The result is that it's in the worst case really  unclear, in the best case just pretty difficult to pinpoint the right data as you have to be absolutely certain which tables come from which database.
Please introduce a separator in all views where the database can be identified - or prepend the database name to the table name until a separate column (with filter option like for tags) can be made available.

integration: Full imports should not block incremental ones
text_content:
We currently have the issue that long running full imports, e.g. shopify for 48 hours with a long shop, prevent incremental imports which is an issue since the customer doesn't want to wait that long for new data.

The idea would that incremental imports keep running on the current main table while the full import is still building up the new one.

integration: Integration - Klaviyo - Import settings - Object flattening
text_content:
Column with nested object not imported after change of "Import setting"

Customer: Wildling
Integration: Klaviyo
Issue subject: Import settings - Object flattening

 
timeline of events:

We have imported the initial data from our customer Wildling from Klaviyo (https://app.datos-i.com/organization/wildling/integrations/view/dd2abc59-4084-45f6-853d-6c1130b17004/structure/integration)
No settings regarding object flattening were set -> all tables with nested objects are imported unnested 
I've set the "Object Flattening" to 1 inside the "Import settings" for the table "receive" for testing purpose to see how results would look like ( -> nested fields "person" and "event_properties" inside the table "receive")
after the re-import finished, the columns "person" and "event_properties" inside the table "receive" were gone /they didn't got imported /no flattened fields were created
changed the object flattening settings for table "receive" back to 0 so  that at least we will have "person" and "event_properties" as columns with nested objects
Re-import still shows data of table "receive" without the columns "person" and "receive"

text_content:
Integration to support custom webhooks.

This way a customer can setup a URL with a schema and can send json requests that are streamed into bigquery this way

Example from Waterdrop:
HTTP-Methode: POST
Content-Type: application/json
{
	"order_id": {{order.id}},
	"order_name": "{{order.name}}",
	"question": "{{trigger.question}}",
	"response": "{{trigger.response}}"
}
 


Documentation Stitch:
https://www.stitchdata.com/docs/integrations/webhooks

text_content:
Our customer is still using the competitor product "Supermetrics" to sanity check our data. He found out that the ads_insights table in the Facebook Ads integration is rounding big numbers. In this case the number is an ID, to be specific the ad_id. The rounded ad_id is therefore not correct anymore. This ID critical to join the table with other Facebook Ads table, therefore quite important. In this case we need define any ID fields as BIG_INT or as TEXT.

The same issue is faced also with other fields:
adset_id
campaign_id
etc.
These ids are used to join with the respective adsets and campaign tables by joining on the ad_id = id. The adset_id and campaign_id although are formatted as number in the ads_insights table and as text in the respective attributes table (adsets and campaign). We have to make this consistent and format the ids in the ads_insights table also text.
